start.desc:
Starts a profiling scope with the specified name, which allows you to measure the performance of script functions or code
			blocks in the in-game profiler.

stop.desc: Stops the last profile scope started by [stingray.Profiler.start()].

record_statistics.desc: Records statistics data (a float or vector3) for the in-game graph drawer.

RIGHT.desc: Represents the right direction in a swipe gesture.

DOWN.desc: Represents the down direction in a swipe gesture.

UP.desc: Represents the up direction in a swipe gesture.

LEFT.desc: Represents the left direction in a swipe gesture.

animation_root_mode.desc: Retrieves the current animation root mode.

world_rotation.desc: Retrieves the world rotation of a node in the unit.

crossfade_animation.desc: Crossfades in the animation on the specified unit in the specified animation layer over the specified blend time.

animation_find_variable.desc: Finds the index of a specified variable in the unit's animation state machine.

has_mesh.desc: Indicates whether or not the unit contains a mesh with the specified name.

box.desc: Retrieves an oriented bounding box that encloses all the meshes in the unit.

ANIMATION_OVERRIDE_PERCENT_SYNC.desc:
integer = <internal>
Overrides the percent value for percent sync transitions in calls to [animation_event()].

get_property.desc:
Retrieves the value of a property on a unit, or on any object owned by the unit, such as a material,
		mesh or light.

scene_graph_parent.desc: Retrieves the parent of a node in the unit's scene graph.

set_animation_state_machine.desc: Sets the animation state machine of the unit to something other than the default.

num_meshes.desc: Retrieves the number of meshes in the unit.

num_actors.desc: Retrieves the number of actors owned by the unit.

set_light_material.desc: Assigns a material resource to a specified light source within the unit.

set_material.desc: Assigns a material resource to a specified material slot within the unit.

delta_pose.desc: Retrieves the delta world position and orientation of a node in the unit since the last frame.

material_id.desc: Retrieves the ID for the material with the specified name, to be used in conjunction with [query_material()].

create_cloth.desc: Creates an Apex cloth with the specified name or index in the unit, if it has not been created already.

num_lights.desc: Retrieves the number of lights in the unit.

query_material.desc:
Finds the closest intersection by doing a raycast from *start* to *end*, and returns a list
		with one material ID per context.

animation_has_constraint_target.desc: Returns *true* if the constraint target is defined for the unit, or *false* otherwise.

set_data.desc:
Stores the specified value in the unit's script data object, at a location determined
		by the specified indices.

node.desc: Retrieves the index of the object node that matches the specified name.

lod_object.desc: Retrieves the specified LOD Object owned by the unit.

world_position.desc: Retrieves the world position of a node in the unit.

stop_simple_animation.desc: Stops a simple animation playing for the unit.

set_angular_velocity.desc: Sets the current angular velocity of the specified [GwNavBoxObstacle].

set_linear_velocity.desc: Sets the current linear velocity of the specified [GwNavBoxObstacle].

set_transform.desc: Sets the current transform of the specified [GwNavBoxObstacle].

remove_from_world.desc: Removes the given [GwNavBoxObstacle] from the nav_world that was specified when it was created.

set_rotation_mode_around_yaw_only.desc: Sets the rotation mode of the [GwNavBoxObstacle], either it will rotate around yaw, or it will rotate freely.

add_to_world.desc: Adds the given [GwNavBoxObstacle] to the world that was specified when it was created.

contacts.desc: Retrieves all contacts that are currently active on the controller.

is_primary.desc: Indicates whether or not the contact with the specified id is considered the primary contact point.

gesture_rotate.desc: Returns nil if there is no active rotation gesture, else returns every value associated with the rotation gesture.

major_axis_size.desc:
Retrieves the size of the specified contact along the major axis: the longer dimension of the contact
		area.

size.desc: Retrieves the size of the specified contact.

is_touch_down.desc: Indicates whether or not the contact with the specified id was initiated in this frame.

num_contacts.desc: Retrieves the number of touch contacts that are currently active on the controller.

accelerator_resolution.desc: Retrieves the accelerator resolution for the controller.

has_contact.desc: Indicates whether or not a contact exists with the specified id.

gesture_swipe.desc: Returns nil if there has been no swipe gesture, else returns the direction of the swipe gesture.

gesture_pinch.desc: Returns nil if there is no active pinch gesture, else returns every value associated with the pinch gesture.

gesture_tap_sequence.desc:
Returns nil if no taps occured, else returns the number of subsequent taps confirmed having occured
		after one another, each tap waits for ~0.35s before confirming there are no more following taps.

location_delta.desc:
Retrieves the difference between the location of the contact in the previous frame and the current
		location of the contact in the current frame.

resolution.desc: Retrieves the resolution of the input coordinates for the controller.

pressure.desc: Retrieves the pressure of the specified contact on the surface of the touch panel.

edge.desc: Indicates the edge that this contact originates from, if any.

gesture_long_press.desc: Returns nil if no long press gesture has occured, else returns the location of where the gesture began.

location.desc: Retrieves the location of the specified contact on the touch panel.

gesture_tap.desc: Returns nil if no tap occured, else returns the location of the most recent non-sequence tap.

minor_axis_size.desc:
Retrieves the size of the specified contact along the minor axis: the shorter dimension of the contact
		area.

is_touch_up.desc: Indicates whether or not the contact with the specified id was released in this frame.

store.desc: Stores the specified quaternion values in the box.

unbox.desc: Retrieves the quaternion last stored in the specified box.

set_game_session_host.desc: Sets the host of the game session to the specified peer.

FAILED.desc:
integer = <internal>
This state indicates that this peer has been rejected by the room host, or has dropped out of the room due
		to a problem such as a bad connection..

JOINING.desc:
integer = <internal>
The state of the room after it has been joined by a call to [Network.join_psn_room()].
		This state means the room is waiting for the room owner to accept this peer as a room member. When this peer is
		accepted, the state changes to [PsnRoom.JOINED]. If this peer is not accepted, the state changes to [PsnRoom.FAILED].

member.desc: Retrieves detailed information about the room member at the specified index.

num_members.desc: Returns the number of members currently in the room.

state.desc: Indicates the current state of the room, and whether or not this peer has joined successfully.

JOINED.desc:
integer = <internal>
Indicates that the player is in the room.

game_session_host.desc: Returns the game session host for the room.

CREATING.desc:
integer = <internal>
Indicates that the creation of the room has started. If the room is successfully created, the state
		changes to [PsnRoom.JOINED]. If the creation fails, the state changes to [PsnRoom.FAILED].

WAITING_TO_CREATE.desc:
integer = <internal>
Indicates that the room is queued to be created, but [PsnClient.ready()] does not yet return *true*. This is the
		state of the room after it has been created with [Network.create_psn_room()]. When [PsnClient.ready()] returns *true*,
		the state changes to [PsnRoom.CREATING].

set_data.desc: Stores a single opaque data value for the room.

set_name.desc: Stores a name for the room.

owner.desc: Retrieves the current owner of the PSN room.

active.desc: Indicates whether or not the controller is *active*: i.e. connected and working as expected.

released.desc: Indicates whether or not the player released the button with the specified id during this frame.

axis.desc: Returns the input value for a single axis of the controller.

button.desc: Returns the current input value of the button with the specified id.

any_pressed.desc: Indicates whether or not the player pressed any buttons at all in the current frame.

pressed.desc: Indicates whether or not the player pressed the button with the specified id during this frame.

type.desc: Returns a description of the hardware device used for this controller.

any_released.desc: Indicates whether or not the player released any buttons at all in the current frame.

axis_id.desc: Retrieves the id of the axis with the specified name in the controller, if any.

button_name.desc: Retrieves the name of the button with the specified id in the controller.

axis_name.desc: Retrieves the name of the axis with the specified id in the controller.

name.desc: Returns a unique name for the controller: e.g. "Xbox Controller 1".

disconnected.desc: Indicates whether or not the controller has been disconnected this frame.

num_axes.desc: Returns the number of axes on the controller.

connected.desc: Indicates whether or not the controller has been attached this frame.

button_id.desc: Retrieves the id of the button with the specified name in the controller, if any.

num_buttons.desc: Returns the number of buttons on the controller.

is_finished.desc: Indicates whether or not the user has finished entering data into the ImeDialog.

show.desc: Shows the PlayStation 4 keyboard input dialog.

is_showing.desc: Indicates whether or not the ImeDialog box is showing.
